organic_results.title: Research note: Correlates of faculty publications
organic_results.snippet: This note uses Multiple Classification Analysis on a national sample of faculty in both four-year colleges (N= 1,216) and universities (N= 7,484) to ascertain the correlates of scholarly productivity. The large sample permits disciplinary breakdowns and makes possible comparisons with prior research done on selected populations, and hence confirms or disconfirms possible generalizations from those works. The principal dependent variables are rate of article production, total articles published, and books published.
